{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The content passed to the summary-generation step includes data retrieved from all three sources.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is module handoff: collectors -> aggregator -> summary-call payload (MOCK-MISS: yes, cross-module wiring). Integration-brake: (a) no real OS/network/subprocess required; source clients can be in-process fakes. (b) no dependence on model output content; assertion is pre-call payload shape/content. (c) no multi-agentic chain. (d) no LLM-governed stage handoff correctness being validated. Rejection-gate: System/Agentic rejected because behavior text is specifically about \"content passed\" to generation, not transport realism or model judgment.","test_description":"Wire real collection/aggregation modules with three stub source adapters returning distinct sentinel fields. Execute one run up to the summary-generation call and assert the exact request payload includes all three source sections/values.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When one data source is unavailable, the report is produced with a `data unavailable` note for that section rather than aborting.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure appears when source-error handling propagates through aggregation and report assembly (MOCK-MISS: cross-module error handoff). Integration-brake: (a) real network/process not required; simulate one source failure in-process. (b) correctness does not require real model quality; check presence of fallback note and successful report completion. (c) no multi-agentic sequence. (d) no planner/tool/critic LLM orchestration dependency. Rejection-gate: System rejected because behavior does not require real outage mechanics, only handling of an unavailable source condition.","test_description":"Run pipeline with two sources returning data and one source raising a timeout/unavailable exception via fake adapter. Assert run does not abort, output report exists, and the failing section contains `data unavailable`.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.07,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.15,"Agentic":0.06,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The narrative summary accurately represents the key values present in the input data.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on actual summary-generation output quality (LLM-DEP: yes). A stubbed generator can always echo expected facts and would hide real hallucination/omission failures (MOCK-HIDE: yes). Single model judgment step, not a multi-agent pipeline, so not Workflow. Rejection-gate: Integration rejected because behavior text requires \"accurately represents\" semantic fidelity, which deterministic stubs cannot validate.","test_description":"Use real summary model/API with fixed representative input datasets. Evaluate output against required key facts (must-include values, no contradictory values, tolerable paraphrase) via strict checks and/or human-labeled rubric over repeated runs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.1,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.8,"Workflow":0.06}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A complete report — from data collection through email delivery — reaches the configured recipient's inbox correctly.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Behavior requires real external boundaries: source APIs + actual email delivery to an inbox (REAL-INFRA: yes). In-process mocks can hide SMTP/provider auth, routing, formatting, and inbox acceptance failures (MOCK-HIDE: yes). Not inherently Agentic because success criterion is end-to-end delivery, not model-output quality. Rejection-gate: Agentic rejected since behavior text focuses on delivery to inbox, not semantic quality of generated narrative.","test_description":"Execute scheduled run in a system test environment against reachable test instances of the three sources and a real test mailbox/service. Assert email is received by configured recipient, with expected subject/body/report structure present.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.78,"Agentic":0.08,"Workflow":0.04}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the email delivery service is unreachable, the generated report is saved to a local file and delivery is retried on the next scheduled run.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Needs real infrastructure boundaries: email transport unreachable condition plus durable local file persistence across runs and scheduler-triggered retry (REAL-INFRA: yes). Mocks often miss filesystem permission/path/timing and retry-on-next-run behavior (MOCK-HIDE: yes). No model-output quality dependency; this is resilience/orchestration around delivery. Rejection-gate: Integration rejected because behavior explicitly requires persistence to local file and retry on next scheduled execution, which is an OS/scheduling boundary.","test_description":"Run once with email endpoint intentionally unreachable; verify report file is persisted to configured local path. Trigger next scheduled run with email restored; verify retry sends previously saved report and clears/marks retry state appropriately.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.1,"System":0.82,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.03}}]}
